wrapScienceJ.metaData.sets

Class MetaDataSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • wrapScienceJ.metaData.container.MetaDataContainer
      • wrapScienceJ.metaData.container.MetaData
        • wrapScienceJ.metaData.container.MetaDataRetriever
          • wrapScienceJ.metaData.sets.MetaDataSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MetaStandardTypes
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Blur3DThresholdOtsuComponents3D.ProcessMetaData, BlurProcess.ProcessMetaData, ConnectedComponentsProcess.ProcessMetaData, ConnectedComponentsSegmentation.ProcessMetaData, ThresholdingProcess.ProcessMetaData

    public class MetaDataSet
extends MetaDataRetriever
implements MetaStandardTypes
    This class allows to construct sets of metadata values, all of which are contained a single MetaData set, i.e. with a single metadata file. The values should then be retrieved for use in the subclasses, which can use the data with base types (double, string, boolean, etc.)
